1088
01:32:47,854 --> 01:32:51,335
The current road design implicitly encourages very fast driving.

1089
01:32:51,815 --> 01:33:00,338
We have a large amount of parking that's underutilized on a day-to-day basis, really wide travel lanes so that yields good sight lines where people feel like they can drive very fast.

1090
01:33:00,918 --> 01:33:04,660
So people frankly are scared to ride their bikes, they're scared to cross the street here.

1091
01:33:05,340 --> 01:33:17,627
I think that we need to narrow the roads, as this plan would do, and impose some traffic calming measures to make the actual travel speeds match the posted speed limit, which is 25 miles an hour here which is not what most people are driving.

1092
01:33:18,247 --> 01:33:23,313
Just the other day right off of Winthrop I was screamed at with my wife by someone driving by an SUV.

1093
01:33:23,874 --> 01:33:33,985
I think we need to have road, road designs that prioritize calm driving, and we should follow design principles that encourage that Ellery Klein has been working with the high school at walk Medford.

1094
01:33:34,626 --> 01:33:44,369
to come up with a statistically robust survey that described how a huge portion of the high school students there would like to ride their bikes to school but they are scared to.

1095
01:33:45,109 --> 01:33:52,771
Just imagine the impact on traffic if we could get some of these kids out of cars that are being driven up and down Winthrop multiple times every day.

1096
01:33:53,611 --> 01:33:56,913
