PB, David Ensign — Herndon, I think this alternative, just like the other ones Todd is very well thought through in regards to taking into consideration all the comments that we've heard.

2321
03:23:20,960 --> 03:23:24,183
and understanding the context of this stretch here.

2322
03:23:24,243 --> 03:23:45,820
So I think this plan does strike a balance between the needs and rights of the general public for improvements in safety of Winthrop Street, as well as respecting the situation of the residents and American Legion as an entity on this stretch as well.

2323
03:23:46,300 --> 03:23:48,342
So with that said,

2324
03:23:49,768 --> 03:23:56,813
Like I keep saying, the more I talk about it, the more I look at it, the more it strikes that balance, and I can appreciate it and in favor of it.

2325
03:23:58,354 --> 03:23:58,794
All right.

2326
03:23:59,074 --> 03:24:16,386
If I'm correct, so the original version kept seven spots by the American Legion and then had buffered bike lanes the rest of the way, which was causing a problem for some of these houses that have shared driveways and aren't fully shared, but are still needing to park on the street.

2327
03:24:19,462 --> 03:24:19,966
But that's...

2328
03:24:23,440 --> 03:24:31,023
Yeah, and the other thing that we talked about, we can't have parking that exists for one to use once a year for voting.

2329
03:24:32,283 --> 03:24:42,747
We did talk internally a little bit about you could do temporary signage on election day, allowing parking in places you would never allow parking.

2330
03:24:43,107 --> 03:24:51,289
It would actually be physically hard if there was the poles of buffered bike lanes to allow temporary parking.

2331
03:24:55,026 --> 03:25:11,873
But, and I realize that this is less parking than they have there now, but we need to have, we need to make this safe for 363 days of the year and, you know.

2332
03:25:14,674 --> 03:25:14,914
Yeah.

2333
03:25:17,915 --> 03:25:23,157
Yeah, I think on those special days, like the once or twice a year,

2334
03:25:24,865 --> 03:25:41,253
I would venture to guess that cyclists would be willing to, you know, deal with temporary closure of a bike lane for one day for community event like voting, perhaps, and then that could be a way to somewhat compromise.

2335
03:25:47,136 --> 03:25:50,417
Okay, so am I hearing that the motion and

2336
03:25:52,858 --> 03:26:07,587
would be to accept the alternative plan from the Winthrop Street Rotary up to Lawrence Road, or a better way is to the improved designed end of the previous accepted bike point.

2337
03:26:08,387 --> 03:26:09,408
Sort of the same idea.

2338
03:26:10,408 --> 03:26:14,270
Is that what is being presented?

2339
03:26:14,651 --> 03:26:17,092
I don't think there's been a motion yet.

2340
03:26:17,332 --> 03:26:21,735
My only reservation here is providing

2341
03:26:22,490 --> 03:26:41,804
parking for, you know, one side of the, providing parking for a section of houses, right, like whatever it is, in front of their houses and the American Legion, but nowhere else really, you know, further up Winthrop Street, right?

2342
03:26:41,904 --> 03:26:47,268
So, you know, I do want to try, that's my only reservation, treating everybody fairly here.

2343
03:26:47,348 --> 03:26:49,930
If we're moving parking on Winthrop Street to make things safer,

2344
03:26:50,510 --> 03:27:02,373
with a buffered bike lane, then why would we be keeping this stretch of parking across from Burbank and Badger Road and American Legion for that matter?

2345
03:27:03,413 --> 03:27:07,954
I know I'm kind of having a conversation with myself, but it's probably important for.

2346
03:27:09,475 --> 03:27:18,317
If I can, I'd like to point out in this compromise, there's an added traffic calming element of the shifting over of the lane in the middle of the block.

2347
03:27:19,017 --> 03:27:21,198
So it creates that sort of slalom feel.

2348
03:27:21,458 --> 03:27:27,140
So it takes away a little bit of the straightaway that people experience now, if that matters.

2349
03:27:27,920 --> 03:27:32,402
Are those dots, are those yellow pylons or bollards?

2350
03:27:34,602 --> 03:27:44,266
At one point, I had potential to add yellow flex posts in the double yellow in that region if it became problematic.

2351
03:27:44,926 --> 03:27:47,887
I made it gradual enough, double the length as required,

2352
03:27:48,503 --> 03:27:51,105
based on traffic engineering standards.

2353
03:27:51,165 --> 03:28:00,570
But if people weren't used to that sort of shift, we could consider flex posts in the middle like we used to have on Main Street over by Carrolls for a little while.

2354
03:28:00,871 --> 03:28:08,235
And these are 10 and a half foot lanes, travel lanes for the vehicle, so that will keep speeds down as well.

2355
03:28:12,518 --> 03:28:16,040
So there's a lot of benefits to this alternative plan.

2356
03:28:17,155 --> 03:28:22,838
I'm just concerned about the, you know, keeping parking here, but not as well.

2357
03:28:22,898 --> 03:28:24,438
I guess we're keeping in front of the condos too.

2358
03:28:25,019 --> 03:28:29,681
So, you know, I'm more on the fence of going with the alternative plan.

2359
03:28:30,881 --> 03:28:43,147
I think it's a significant improvement here, but regardless, we have a significant improvement to public safety happening on this alternative plan right now.

2360
03:28:44,460 --> 03:28:49,043
Yeah, going back to that graphic I showed at the very beginning about the relative safety.

2361
03:28:49,864 --> 03:28:59,330
Any of these proposals are more safe for cyclists in the existing conditions, which is a 19 slash 20 foot wide traveling when nobody's parked on the side.

2362
03:28:59,891 --> 03:29:03,333
And then when someone's parked on the side it's, you know, 1213 for traveling.

2363
03:29:03,493 --> 03:29:08,577
So, yeah, so either way we're increasing but yeah it's all relative, and I will say.

2364
03:29:09,837 --> 03:29:27,743
for everyone, for the traffic commission and for anyone watching, you know, even though we're doing engineering standards and engineering practice with all these drawings and proposals, ultimately this value judgment that is being had tonight would still be there no matter what.

2365
03:29:27,763 --> 03:29:35,285
So regardless of what form or how many meetings were, you know, led up to this, each community

2366
03:29:36,016 --> 03:29:42,119
throughout the region is going through the same value judgments in the same transitions in their neighborhoods in their cities.

2367
03:29:42,739 --> 03:29:43,900
And it's not an easy one.

2368
03:29:44,500 --> 03:29:47,082
But there's only so much curb to curb space.

2369
03:29:47,522 --> 03:29:51,004
And this is this is what's going on elsewhere.

2370
03:29:51,024 --> 03:29:51,964
So it's not unique.

2371
03:29:52,624 --> 03:29:55,026
And it's it's not going to go away.

2372
03:29:55,086 --> 03:29:57,047
There's there's pros and cons.

2373
03:29:57,207 --> 03:29:58,227
And it's a balancing act.

2374
03:29:58,287 --> 03:30:00,088
And I appreciate the commission's time.

2375
03:30:00,829 --> 03:30:00,929
And

2376
03:30:02,321 --> 03:30:03,902
looking at this in a very thoughtful way.

2377
03:30:03,942 --> 03:30:06,623
And I appreciate our community attending as well.

2378
03:30:08,183 --> 03:30:08,464
Thanks.

2379
03:30:08,484 --> 03:30:15,206
Maybe I'll let Alicia make the motion on this one.

2380
03:30:15,226 --> 03:30:18,107
All right.

2381
03:30:20,448 --> 03:30:29,092
So a motion to approve the alternate version that preserves the parking for this stretch.

2382
03:30:30,748 --> 03:30:33,671
So from the circle to Lawrence road.

2383
03:30:33,691 --> 03:30:37,975
I'll second.

2384
03:30:37,995 --> 03:30:39,957
Okay.

2385
03:30:40,117 --> 03:30:55,291
So motion by commissioner hot to approve the alternative, uh, plan all the way to Lawrence road, which for the record would be where the approved, the current approved design ends.

2386
03:31:00,495 --> 03:31:01,196
Alva, roll call vote?

2387
03:31:01,216 --> 03:31:02,316
To preserve parking.

2388
03:31:02,757 --> 03:31:03,477
To preserve, yeah.

2389
03:31:03,497 --> 03:31:05,258
Well, the alternative plan is preserve parking.

2390
03:31:05,298 --> 03:31:06,199
Yes, to preserve parking.

2391
03:31:06,579 --> 03:31:06,799
Okay.

2392
